-- Pimco Total Return Fund behind 87 percent of its peers so far this year  
-- By Jennifer Ablan
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 09:43AM EDT
-- None



March 28 (Reuters) - The Pimco Total Return Fund, the world's largest bond fund run by Bill Gross, is trailing 87 percent of its peers so far this year despite returning to gains after a rough 2013, Morningstar data show on Friday.

